%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%22Rishi%20Sunak%E2%80%99s%20Last%20Stand%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F04085015%2FLC.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELondon%20Calling%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%C2%A0How%20does%20India%20look%20from%20afar%3F%20Looming%20world%20power%20or%20dysfunctional%20democracy%3F%20And%20what%E2%80%99s%20happening%20in%20Britain%2C%20and%20the%20West%2C%20that%20India%20needs%20to%20know%20about%20and%20perhaps%20learn%20from%3F%20This%20fortnightly%20column%20helps%20forge%20the%20connections%20so%20essential%20in%20our%20globalising%20world.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%E2%80%99s%20Rishi%20Sunak%E2%80%99s%20nightmare.%20As%20his%20Conservative%20Party%20gathers%20for%20probably%20its%20last%20annual%20conference%20before%20an%20election%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20been%20plunged%20into%20a%20row%20about%20race%20and%20multiculturalism.%20And%20a%20supposed%20political%20ally%20of%20Sunak%E2%80%99s%20lit%20the%20fuse.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESuella%20Braverman%2C%20the%20home%20secretary%20and%20herself%20of%20East%20African%20and%20Goan%20heritage%2C%20delivered%20an%20incendiary%20speech%20last%20week%20denouncing%20the%20%E2%80%98misguided%20dogma%E2%80%99%20of%20multiculturalism.%20She%20argued%20that%20%E2%80%98multiculturalism%20makes%20no%20demands%20of%20the%20incomer%20to%20integrate.%20It%20has%20failed%20because%20it%20allowed%20people%20to%20come%20to%20our%20society%20and%20live%20parallel%20lives%20in%20it.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20370px)%2085vw%2C%20370px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F04%2F20115409%2Funnamed.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22370%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F04%2F20115409%2Funnamed.jpg%20526w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F04%2F20115409%2Funnamed-247x300.jpg%20247w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-649461%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22450%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EIllustration%3A%20Pariplab%20Chakraborty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EHer%20speech%20extended%20into%20a%20wide-ranging%20criticism%20of%20immigration%20policy%2C%20one%20of%20her%20key%20ministerial%20responsibilities.%20In%20recent%20years%20immigration%20had%20been%20%E2%80%98too%20much%2C%20too%20many%E2%80%99%2C%20she%20said%2C%20and%20posed%20an%20%E2%80%98existential%20threat%E2%80%99%20to%20Britain%E2%80%99s%20way%20of%20life.%20What%20Braverman%20described%20as%20the%20%E2%80%98toxic%20combination%E2%80%99%20of%20uncontrolled%20immigration%20and%20the%20failure%20to%20integrate%20new%20migrants%20was%20creating%20%E2%80%98the%20conditions%20for%20more%20extreme%20politics%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20not%20just%20a%20passing%20comment%20in%20a%20TV%20interview.%20The%20home%20secretary%20made%20her%20remarks%20in%20a%20speech%20at%20a%20think%20tank%20in%20Washington%20DC.%20It%E2%80%99s%20a%20well%20thought%20through%20strategy%20to%20throw%20a%20spotlight%20on%20immigration%20and%20integration%20%E2%80%93%20and%20a%20spotlight%20too%2C%20of%20course%2C%20on%20the%20deeply%20ambitious%20politician%20who%20delivered%20the%20speech.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBraverman%20was%20promptly%20slapped%20down%20by%20the%20prime%20minister.%20Britain%20%E2%80%98is%20a%20fantastic%20multicultural%20democracy%E2%80%99%2C%20Sunak%20declared.%20%E2%80%98We%20have%20done%20an%20incredible%20job%20of%20integrating%20people%20into%20society.%E2%80%99%20He%20spoke%20of%20how%20he%20was%20%E2%80%98the%20first%20person%20from%20my%20background%20to%20hold%20this%20job.%20That%E2%80%99s%20a%20wonderful%20thing%2C%20but%20it%E2%80%99s%20also%20not%20a%20big%20deal%20in%20our%20country.%20I%20think%20that%20speaks%20to%20the%20progress%20we%E2%80%99ve%20made%20over%20the%20years.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOther%20prominent%20Conservatives%20of%20colour%20joined%20the%20clamour%20over%20the%20home%20secretary%E2%80%99s%20remarks.%20The%20foreign%20secretary%2C%20James%20Cleverly%20%E2%80%93%20who%20is%20of%20African%20heritage%20%E2%80%93%20pointedly%20remarked%20that%20the%20fact%20there%20are%20so%20many%20prominent%20ministers%20from%20ethnic%20minorities%20showed%20that%20Britain%20had%20been%20%E2%80%98brilliant%20at%20integrating%20people%20who%20have%20come%20to%20this%20country%E2%80%99.%20A%20former%20home%20secretary%2C%20Priti%20Patel%2C%20accused%20Braverman%20of%20making%20the%20speech%20simply%20to%20%E2%80%98get%20attention%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20row%20is%20a%20symptom%20of%20divisions%20within%20the%20Conservative%20Party%20at%20a%20time%20when%20it%20needs%20to%20come%20across%20as%20united.%20The%20Conservative%20Party%20conference%20is%20now%20underway%20in%20the%20northern%20city%20of%20Manchester.%20And%20the%20grim%20truth%20is%20that%20hardly%20anyone%20gathered%20in%20the%20conference%20venue%20expects%20the%20party%20to%20retain%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20next%20election%20has%20to%20be%20held%20by%20January%202025%20but%20the%20exact%20timing%20is%20in%20the%20hands%20of%20the%20government.%20Commentators%20believe%20the%20most%20likely%20polling%20date%20is%20in%20about%20a%20year%E2%80%99s%20time.%20So%20this%20will%20be%20the%20last%20party%20conference%20season%20before%20the%20country%20becomes%20engulfed%20in%20an%20election%20campaign.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20Rishi%20Sunak%E2%80%99s%2012%20months%20in%20the%20top%20job%2C%20he%20has%20succeeded%20in%20reassuring%20the%20financial%20markets%2C%20improved%20relations%20with%20the%20European%20Union%20and%20resolved%20the%20hugely%20tricky%20problem%20of%20Northern%20Ireland%E2%80%99s%20post-Brexit%20status.%20But%20the%20government%20lacks%20direction%20and%20has%20proved%20unable%20to%20get%20on%20top%20of%20the%20cost%20of%20living%20crisis%20and%20profound%20problems%20affecting%20the%20state-financed%20National%20Health%20Service.%20Opinion%20polls%20consistently%20point%20to%20a%20commanding%20lead%20for%20the%20opposition%20Labour%20Party.%20The%20Conservatives%20are%20likely%20to%20face%20not%20so%20much%20a%20defeat%20as%20a%20drubbing%20when%20the%20country%20votes.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20public%20seems%20to%20have%20come%20to%20a%20collective%20decision%20%E2%80%93%20that%20the%20Conservatives%20have%20been%20in%20power%20for%20too%20long%2C%2013%20years%20and%20counting%2C%20and%20it%E2%80%99s%20time%20for%20a%20change.%20The%20scandals%20surrounding%20Boris%20Johnson%2C%20and%20then%20the%20catastrophe%20of%20Liz%20Truss%E2%80%99s%20brief%20tenure%20when%20the%20financial%20markets%20lost%20confidence%20in%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20ability%20to%20balance%20the%20books%2C%20have%20stripped%20away%20all%20but%20core%2C%20unshakable%20Conservative%20supporters.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMany%20prominent%20Conservatives%20are%20now%20looking%20to%20what%20happens%20after%20an%20election%20defeat.%20If%20it%E2%80%99s%20as%20bad%20as%20seems%20likely%2C%20Sunak%20will%20almost%20certainly%20resign%20straight%20away%20as%20party%20leader.%20Braverman%20is%20one%20of%20those%20aspiring%20to%20succeed%20him.%20Her%20support%20base%20is%20among%20the%20determinedly%20ideological%20free%20marketeers%20and%20social%20conservatives%20who%20make%20up%20a%20surprisingly%20large%20part%20of%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20grassroots%20membership.%20And%20she%E2%80%99s%20not%20the%20only%20minister%20who%20is%20positioning%20themselves%20for%20life%20after%20Sunak.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20all%20makes%20the%20prime%20minister%E2%80%99s%20job%20even%20more%20impossible.%20He%20needs%20to%20convince%20the%20electorate%20that%20the%20Conservatives%20are%20confident%20and%20coherent%20when%20everyone%20can%20see%20that%20the%20party%20is%20succumbing%20to%20feuding%20and%20factionalising.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAs%20for%20Braverman%E2%80%99s%20comments%20on%20multiculturalism%2C%20there%20is%20unease%20that%20the%20integration%20of%20some%20ethnic%20groups%20has%20been%20painfully%20slow.%20Many%20people%20regard%20themselves%20as%20Black%20British%2C%20or%20British%20Asian%2C%20rather%20than%20simply%20British.%20That%20in%20part%20is%20a%20response%20to%20the%20racism%20they%20have%20encountered.%20And%20western%20nations%20that%20proclaim%20the%20importance%20of%20assimilation%20%E2%80%93%20notably%20France%20%E2%80%93%20have%20not%20been%20much%20more%20successful%20in%20integrating%20the%20children%20of%20those%20who%20migrated%20from%20former%20French%20colonies%20in%20North%20and%20West%20Africa.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20there%E2%80%99s%20also%20suspicion%20that%20the%20home%20secretary%E2%80%99s%20crusade%20against%20multiculturalism%20is%20intended%20to%20mask%20the%20failure%20to%20clamp%20down%20on%20illegal%20migration%20across%20the%20Channel%20in%20small%2C%20overcrowded%20and%20desperately%20unsafe%20boats%20and%20dinghies.%20Although%20the%20overall%20numbers%20are%20not%20huge%2C%20public%20opinion%20is%20alarmed%20by%20Sunak%E2%80%99s%20inability%20to%20tackle%20this%20hazardous%20and%20illegal%20form%20of%20migration.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20judging%20by%20the%20political%20mood%20of%20the%20country%2C%20that%20won%E2%80%99t%20be%20Sunak%E2%80%99s%20headache%20for%20much%20longer.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAndrew%20Whitehead%20is%20an%20honorary%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Nottingham%20in%20the%20UK%20and%20a%20former%20BBC%20India%20Correspondent.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696389665000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F04085015%2FLC.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Frishi-sunaks-last-stand%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Suella%20Braverman's%20recent%20remarks%20and%20the%20row%20they%20have%20created%20are%20a%20symptom%20of%20divisions%20within%20the%20Conservative%20Party%20at%20a%20time%20