3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20open%20a%20bottle%2C%20you%20share%20it%20with%20some%20friends%2C%20and%20you%20tell%20stories%20to%20each%20other%20about%20what's%20happening%20in%20each%20other's%20lives%2C%26quot%3B%20Soto%2C%20who's%20from%20Costa%20Rica%2C%20told%20Insider.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENosotros%20started%20as%20a%20business-school%20assignment.%20In%202016%2C%20the%20company%20launched%20its%20first%20batch%20of%20tequila.%20At%20the%20time%2C%20the%20business%20was%20considered%20an%20underdog%20in%20a%20market%20dominated%20by%20legacy%20brands%2C%20Arbanas%20told%20Insider.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225546%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Headshot%20of%20Michael%20Arbanas%2C%20wearing%20a%20dark%20gray%20shirt%20in%20front%20of%20a%20light%20gray%20background.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65170fe23fb8f400198ad8b4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224160%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMichael%20Arbanas%2C%20a%20cofounder%20of%20Nosotros%20Tequila%20%26amp%3B%20Mezcal.%3Cp%3ENosotros%20Tequila%20%26amp%3B%20Mezcal%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20stand%20out%2C%20the%20Los%20Angeles%20company%20focused%20on%20its%20grassroots%20origins%2C%20Latino%20ownership%2C%20and%20commitment%20to%20sustainable%20farming%20in%20Mexico%2C%20where%20most%20of%20its%20tequila%20is%20produced%20by%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nosotrostequila.com%2Fcopy-of-story%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewoman-owned%20and%20-operated%20distillery%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Soto%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20elements%20have%20helped%20the%20cofounders%20create%20a%20compelling%2C%20authentic%20brand%20story%20that%20continues%20to%20resonate%20with%20people%20and%20draw%20in%20business.%20Today%2C%20Nosotros%20products%20are%20available%20in%2042%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20how%20to%20write%20and%20tell%20a%20brand%20story%2C%20and%20why%20it's%20important%20for%20attracting%20customers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EBuild%20authentic%20connections%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20brand%20story%20is%20the%20%26quot%3Bwhy%20behind%20the%20business%2C%26quot%3B%20Matt%20Johnson%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.neuroscienceof.com%2Fbranding-blog%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebranding%20psychologist%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20author%20of%20%26quot%3BBranding%20That%20Means%20Business%2C%26quot%3B%20told%20Insider.%20Small%20businesses%20resonate%20more%20with%20customers%20when%20they%20share%20their%20backgrounds%20and%20deeper%20motivations%2C%20beyond%20trying%20to%20sell%20products%20or%20services.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20constructing%20a%20brand%20story%2C%20small%20businesses%20should%20curate%20elements%20that%20resonate%20most%20with%20the%20target%20consumer%20%E2%80%94%20but%20the%20story%20must%20be%20true%20and%20authentic%2C%20he%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22668%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Headshot%20of%20Matt%20Johnson%2C%20wearing%20a%20gray%20blazer%20and%20blue%20shirt.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6517183311c4f900199150ec%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22501%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMatt%20Johnson%2C%20a%20branding%20psychologist%20and%20author%20of%20%E2%80%9CBranding%20That%20Means%20Business.%E2%80%9D%3Cp%3EPrince%20Ghuman%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EForrester%20research%20indicated%20that%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.forrester.com%2Fblogs%2Fconsumers-crave-authenticity-and-cmos-can-deliver%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eseven%20in%2010%20US%20consumers%3C%2Fa%3E%20related%20to%20authentic%20brands%20and%20wanted%20to%20support%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat's%20made%20our%20story%20so%20powerful%20is%20we're%20not%20going%20out%20of%20our%20way%20to%20curate%20something%20that%20doesn't%20fit%20what%20we%20do%20on%20a%20daily%20basis%20or%20how%20we%20look%20at%20life%20or%20the%20things%20that%20we%20value%2C%26quot%3B%20Soto%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20a%20community%20of%20more%20than%2024%2C000%20followers%20on%20Instagram%2C%20Nosotros%20highlights%20its%20origins%20and%20promotes%20wellness%20and%20drinking%20responsibly.%20It%20also%20encourages%20customers%20to%20share%20their%20stories%20and%20how%20they%20relate%20to%20the%20brand.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20consumer%2C%20Soto%20said%20he%20appreciated%20brands%20when%20he%20could%20%26quot%3Breally%20feel%20the%20pains%20that%20person%20has%20gone%20through%20to%20make%20something%20real%2C%26quot%3B%20adding%20that%20he%20believed%20that's%20more%20compelling%20than%20traditional%20advertising.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ETell%20your%20origin%20story%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20of%20a%20small%20business'%20marketing%2C%20including%20branded%20content%20and%20social-media%20posts%2C%20should%20tell%20and%20retell%20the%20brand%20story%2C%20Johnson%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BThat's%20how%2C%20ultimately%2C%20you%20develop%20brand%20awareness.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHelping%20consumers%20understand%20the%20motivation%20behind%20the%20company%20creates%20an%20emotional%20connection%2C%20builds%20loyalty%2C%20and%20distinguishes%20a%20small%20business%2C%20Johnson%20said.%20To%20accomplish%20that%2C%20you%20need%20to%20get%20to%20know%20your%20customers.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20you%20understand%20your%20customers%2C%20you%20can%20learn%20which%20stories%20best%20showcase%20your%20products%20or%20services%20and%20inspire%20them%20to%20do%20business%20with%20you%2C%20he%20said.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EBack%20it%20up%20with%20quality%20products%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20compelling%20brand%20story%20is%20worthless%20without%20a%20solid%20product%20to%20back%20it%20up%2C%20Arbanas%20said.%20Nosotros%20offers%20a%20variety%20of%20tequila%20and%20mezcal%20products%2C%20and%20its%20%26quot%3Bdrink%20less%2C%20drink%20better%26quot%3B