nuary%2006%2C%202023%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC.%3Cp%3EKevin%20Dietsch%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%20%3Cli%3ETo%20become%20speaker%20of%20the%20House%2C%20Kevin%20McCarthy%20was%20forced%20to%20make%20several%20concessions.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EHe%20agreed%20to%20change%20House%20rules%20to%20allow%20any%20member%20to%20bring%20a%20motion%20to%20vacate%20the%20speakership.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3ELess%20than%20a%20year%20later%2C%20the%20decision%20is%20already%20coming%20back%20to%20haunt%20him.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAbout%20nine%20months%20after%20getting%20elected%20as%20speaker%20of%20the%20House%2C%20Kevin%20McCarthy's%20days%20as%20the%20top%20Republican%20in%20Congress'%20lower%20chamber%20appear%20to%20be%20numbered.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20shouldn't%20come%20as%20any%20surprise%20to%20him%2C%20though%2C%20after%20he%20personally%20sacrificed%20any%20chance%20of%20stability%20to%20attain%20the%20speakership%20in%20the%20first%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20January%2C%20just%20a%20few%20short%20months%20after%20an%20election%20where%20Republicans%20just%20barely%20gained%20majority%20control%20of%20the%20House%20of%20Representatives%2C%20McCarthy%20had%20emerged%20as%20the%20frontrunner%20to%20become%20the%20next%20House%20speaker.%20And%20while%20he%20clearly%20had%20the%20most%20support%20in%20the%20conference%2C%20his%20path%20to%20getting%20the%20role%20was%20anything%20but%20typical.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETraditionally%2C%20it%20only%20takes%20one%20ballot%20and%20less%20than%20one%20day%20to%20elect%20a%20speaker%2C%20and%20the%20victor%20only%20needs%20a%20simple%20majority%20vote%20to%20ascend%20to%20the%20speakership.%20In%20McCarthy's%20case%2C%20however%2C%20it%20took%20the%20House%20several%20prolonged%20days%20and%20fifteen%20votes%20to%20ultimately%20narrowly%20elect%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMcCarthy's%20ascension%20to%20becoming%20the%20speaker%20of%20the%20House%20didn't%20come%20without%20a%20cost.%20It%20came%20with%20several%20concessions%20to%20win%20over%20enough%20Republican%20holdouts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20agreeing%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkevin-mccarthy-ended-proxy-voting-it-could-cost-the-gop-2023-1%5C%22%3Edisallow%20members%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20voting%20via%20proxy%2C%20limitations%20on%20spending%20bills%2C%20and%20bringing%20back%20a%2019th-century%20rule%20allowing%20legislators%20to%20reduce%20the%20salaries%20of%20federal%20employees%2C%20McCarthy%20made%20a%20key%20concession%20that's%20finally%20come%20back%20to%20haunt%20him%3A%20allowing%20any%20single%20House%20member%20to%20file%20a%20%26quot%3Bmotion%20to%20vacate%26quot%3B%20in%20an%20attempt%20to%20boot%20him%20from%20his%20seat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20congressional%20precedent%20for%20making%20it%20so%20simple%20to%20start%20such%20deliberations%20as%20it%20was%20the%20standard%20modus%20operandi%20for%20more%20than%20a%20century%20before%20House%20Democrats%20adjusted%20the%20rules%20under%20former%20Speaker%20Nancy%20Pelosi%20to%20make%20the%20process%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dallasnews.com%2Fnews%2Fpolitifact%2F2023%2F10%2F03%2Fmatt-gaetzs-motion-to-vacate-the-house-speakership-what-to-know%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emore%20difficult%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20initiate%20by%20preventing%20the%20motions%20from%20moving%20forward%20unless%20they%20were%20filed%20%26quot%3Bby%20direction%20of%20a%20party%20caucus%20or%20conference.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EApproximately%20nine%20months%20after%20he%20agreed%20to%20switch%20back%20to%20the%20%26quot%3Bsingle-vote%26quot%3B%20method%20to%20offer%20a%20motion%20to%20vacate%2C%20a%20lone%20Republican%20has%20taken%20the%20opportunity%20and%20done%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20McCarthy%20relied%20on%20congressional%20Democrats%20in%20September%20to%20reach%20a%20solution%20to%20temporarily%20keep%20the%20government%20funded%2C%20GOP%20firebr