austerity%2C%20and%20integrity%20of%20the%20higher%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EKamaraj%20was%20born%20on%20July%2015%2C%201902%2C%20in%20a%20family%20struggling%20to%20make%20ends%20meet.%20His%20father%20died%20when%20he%20was%20only%20six%20years%20old.%20Kamaraj%20had%20to%20drop%20out%20of%20school%20as%20his%20mother%20could%20not%20afford%20to%20the%20fees.%20At%20the%20age%20of%2012%2C%20Kamaraj%20joined%20his%20uncle%E2%80%99s%20clothing%20store%20as%20a%20salesman%20but%20the%20fledgling%20Indian%20nationalist%20movement%20attracted%20his%20attention.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20news%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fjallianawala-bagh-majoritarianism-dyerism-gandhi%5C%22%3EJallianwala%20Bagh%20massacre%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Punjab%20on%20April%2013%2C%201919%20spread%20like%20wildfire%20throughout%20the%20country.%20Virudhnagar%2C%20the%20birthplace%20of%20Kamaraj%2C%20was%20no%20exception.%20The%2016-year-old%20Kamaraj%20joined%20the%20Indian%20National%20Congress%20and%20engaged%20in%20organising%20meetings%20in%20Virudhnagar%20and%20neighbouring%20areas.%20He%20later%20went%20on%20to%20become%20the%20president%20of%20the%20party.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20participated%20in%20the%20non-cooperation%20movement%20in%201921%2C%20but%20his%20family%20did%20not%20support%20his%20involvement%20in%20politics%2C%20and%20sent%20him%20to%20Trivandrum%20(now%20Thiruvananthapuram)%20to%20work%20in%20a%20timber%20shop%20owned%20by%20his%20uncle.%20But%20Kamaraj%E2%80%99s%20interest%20in%20politics%20did%20not%20wane%20and%20he%20joined%20the%20Vaikom%20Satyagraha%20in%20Travancore.%20He%20fought%20for%20the%20rights%20of%20the%20people%20belonging%20to%20the%20lower%20castes%2C%20who%20weren%E2%80%99t%20allowed%20to%20enter%20the%20streets%20near%20the%20temples.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20success%20of%20the%20Vaikom%20Satyagraha%20in%201925%2C%20he%20returned%20to%20Virudhnagar%2C%20where%20he%20plunged%20full-time%20into%20the%20freedom%20struggle.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%201923%2C%20Kamaraj%20met%20Sathyamurthy%2C%20who%2C%20along%20with%20C.%20Rajagopalachari%20(Rajaji)%2C%20was%20among%20the%20tallest%20leaders%20of%20the%20Madras%20Presidency.%20The%2020-year-old%20Kamaraj%20adopted%20Sathyamurthy%20as%20his%20political%20guru.%20This%20would%20pay%20him%20rich%20dividends%20in%20the%20future%20conflicts%20with%20Rajaji%2C%20who%20was%20the%20arch-rival%20of%20Sathyamurthy.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%201930%2C%20Kamaraj%20took%20part%20in%20the%20Salt%20Satyagraha%20Movement%20and%20was%20sentenced%20to%20two%20years%20of%20imprisonment.%20By%20the%20time%20the%20Quit%20India%20Movement%20ended%2C%20Kamaraj%20had%20been%20to%20prison%20six%20times%20and%20had%20spent%20years%20in%20British%20jails.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%201940%2C%20with%20the%20help%20of%20Sathyamurthy%2C%20he%20was%20elected%20as%20the%20president%20of%20the%20Tamil%20Nadu%20Congress%20Committee%2C%20defeating%20his%20opponent%2C%20supported%20by%20Rajaji%2C%20by%20a%20narrow%20margin%20of%20103%20to%20100%20votes.%20He%20held%20this%20post%20till%201954.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20time%2C%20Rajaji%20%E2%80%93%20who%20was%20the%20sitting%20chief%20minister%20for%20the%20second%20time%20%E2%80%93%20had%20become%20unpopular%2C%20and%20Kamaraj%2C%20in%20a%20dexterous%20move%2C%20persuaded%20him%20to%20step%20down%20on%20health%20grounds.%20Then%20Kamaraj%20became%20the%20chief%20minister%2C%20defeating%20C.%20Subramanian%2C%20Rajaji%E2%80%99s%20candidate%2C%20by%2093%20to%2041%20votes.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%20The%20%E2%80%9Cgolden%20age%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EKamaraj%20took%20over%20as%20chief%20minister%20of%20Madras%20on%20April%2013%2C%201954.%20This%20was%20the%20beginning%20of%20what%20is%20described%20as%20the%20%E2%80%9Cgolden%20age%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20history%20of%20post-independence%20Madras%20state%20(now%20Tamil%20Nadu).%20His%20first%20major%20reform%20was%20to%20provide%20free%20and%20compulsory%20primary%20education%20to%20all%20children%20in%20the%20rural%20areas.%20He%20also%20ensured%20that%20there%20was%20no%20village%20in%20the%20whole%20state%20that%20didn%E2%80%99t%20have%20at%20least%20one%20school%20and%20a%20teacher.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETo%20encourage%20parents%20to%20send%20their%20children%20to%20school%2C%20he%20introduced%20the%20free%20midday%20meal%20scheme%20for%20both%20rural%20and%20urban%20children.%20This%20was%20indeed%20an%20innovative%20idea%20which%20was%20later%20improved%20upon%20by%20the%20MGR%20government.%20It%20later%20became%20a%20central%20scheme%20when%20Indira%20Gandhi%20came%20back%20to%20power%20in%201980.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fwhat-a-first-hand-experience-of-midday-meals-taught-a-chennai-man-about-equality%5C%22%3EWhat%20a%20First-Hand%20Experience%20of%20Midday%20Meals%20Taught%20a%20Chennai%20Man%20About%20Equality%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20United%20Progressive%20Alliance%20(UPA)%20government%20further%20expanded%20this%20programme%2C%20which%20has%20now%20become%20a%20universally%20accepted%20scheme%20which%20no%20government%20can%20roll%20back.%20By%20harnessing%20irrigation%20power%2C%20Kamaraj%20turned%20a%20food-deficit%20state%20into%20a%20food-surplus%20state.%20But%20the%20best%20was%20yet%20to%20come.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EKamaraj%20appointed%20R.%20Venkataraman%20(later%20President%20of%20India)%2C%20as%20his%20minister%20for%20industries%20and%20gave%20him%20a%20free%20hand%20to%20execute%20his%20vision%20of%20making%20Madras%20a%20top%20industrial%20state.%20Steel%2C%20power%2C%20cement%2C%20and%20chemical%20industries%20were%20developed%20throughout%20the%20state.%20The%20government%20ensured%20that%20all%20industries%20and%20plants%20were%20evenly%20distributed%20throughout%20the%20state%20and%20no%20region%20was%20offered%20any%20special%20treatment.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20ran%20a%20clean%20and%20honest%20government%20by%20setting%20a%20personal%20example.%20He%20expected%20his%20subordinates%20to%20follow%20his%20example.%20He%20himself%20drew%20inspiration%20from%20Prime%20Minister%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%2C%20who%20by%20the%20end%20of%20the%201950s%20had%20emerged%20on%20the%20world%20stage%20as%20the%20%E2%80%9Cmoral%20leader%20of%20mankind%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20%E2%80%98Kamaraj%20Plan%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBy%201963%2C%20Kamaraj%E2%80%99s%20ninth%20year%20as%20chief%20minister%2C%20and%20Nehru%E2%80%99s%2016th%20year%20as%20prime%20minister%2C%20the%20popularity%20of%20the%20grand%20old%20party%20had%20waned.%20In%20May%201963%2C%20the%20party%20lost%20three%20by-elections%20to%20the%20Lok%20Sabha.%20Three%20opposition%20stalwarts%20%E2%80%93%20Acharya%20Kripalani%2C%20Ram%20Manohar%20Lohia%20and%20Minoo%20Masani%20%E2%80%93%20were%20elected%20to%20parliament%20even%20though%20the%20Congress%20tried%20its%20best%20to%20defeat%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20at%20this%20point%20that%20Nehru%20called%20Kamaraj%20to%20Hyderabad%20to%20discuss%20a%20plan%20he%20had%20earlier%20submitted%20for%20reinvigorating%20the%20party.%20When%20Kamaraj%20submitted%20his%20proposal%2C%20he%20had%20only%20Madras%20in%20mind.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20resigned%20from%20the%20post%20of%20chief%20minister%20to%20focus%20on%20strengthening%20the%20party%20organisation%20in%20the%20state%2C%20and%20to%20counter%20the%20growing%20influence%20of%20the%20Dravida%20Munnetra%20Kazhagam%20(DMK).%20But%20Nehru%20told%20him%20the%20strategy%20should%20apply%20to%20the%20whole%20of%20India%20and%20asked%20him%20to%20raise%20this%20issue%20at%20the%20next%20Congress%20Working%20Committee%20(CWC)%2C%20which%20was%20to%20meet%20shortly.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EUnder%20the%20proposal%2C%20all%20Union%20ministers%20and%20chief%20ministers%20were%20expected%20to%20submit%20their%20resignations%20to%20the%20prime%20minister.%20Nehru%20christened%20the%20plan%20as%20the%20%E2%80%98Kamaraj%20Plan%E2%80%99%20and%20accepted%20the%20resignations%20of%20six%20Union%20ministers%20and%20six%20chief%20ministers.%20Among%20the%20Union%20ministers%20who%20had%20resigned%20were%20Morarji%20Desai%2C%20Lal%20Bahadur%20Shastri%20and%20Jagjivan%20Ram.%20The%20chief%20ministers%20included%20Kamaraj%20(Madras)%2C%20Biju%20Patnaik%20(Orissa%20%5Bnow%20Odisha%5D)%20and%20C.B.%20Gupta%20(Uttar%20Pradesh).%20Nehru%20also%20resigned%20but%20Kamaraj%20and%20the%20CWC%20refused%20to%20accept%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESoon%20after%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jstor.org%2Fstable%2F2642538%5C%22%3EKamaraj%20Plan%3C%2Fa%3E%20came%20into%20effect%2C%20he%20was%20unanimously%20elected%20as%20the%20president%20of%20the%20Indian%20National%20Congress%2C%20even%20though%20then%20home%20minister%20Lal%20Bahadur%20Shastri%20was%20among%20the%20names%20that%20did%20the%20rounds.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENehru%20died%20on%20May%2027%2C%201964.%20It%20was%20natural%20that%20the%20Congress%20president%2C%20who%20had%20the%20experience%20of%20being%20an%20extremely%20successful%20chief%20minister%20for%20a%20decade%2C%20will%20be%20considered%20as%20a%20serious%20candidate.%20But%20in%20his%20typical%20style%2C%20Kamaraj%20set%20at%20rest%20all%20speculations%20about%20him%3A%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewirehindi.com%2F13358%2Fveteran-congress-leader-k-kamaraj-legacy%2F%5C%22%3ENo%20English.%20No%20Hindi.%20How%20%5Bcould%20he%20become%20PM%5D%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fculture%2Fas-india-turns-75-heres-a-list-of-75-indians-of-incredible-consequence%5C%22%3EAs%20India%20Turns%2075%2C%20Here%E2%80%99s%2075%20Debates%20for%20Argumentative%20Indians%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThough%20there%20were%20other%20aspirants%2C%20too%2C%20the%20choice%20ultimately%20narrowed%20down%20to%20Morarji%20Desai%2C%20supported%20by%20the%20right-wing%20and%20leaders%20such%20as%20Jagjivan%20Ram%2C%20former%20INC%20president%20D.%20Sanjeevaya%20and%20Odisha%20chief%20minister%20Biju%20Patnaik.%20But%20like%20the%20mythological%20Pandavas%20who%20had%20Krishna%20on%20their%20side%2C%20Shastri%20had%20the%20support%20of%20not%20only%20Kamaraj%20but%20also%20Indira%20Gandhi%2C%20who%20had%20declined%20to%20be%20in%20the%20contest%20as%20she%20was%2C%20within%20days%20of%20her%20father%E2%80%99s%20death%2C%20%E2%80%99emotionally%20ill-prepared%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20matter%20of%20just%20two%20days%2C%20Kamaraj%20moved%20swiftly%20and%20met%20nearly%20250%20MPs%20and%20convinced%20them%20to%20support%20Shastri.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDesai%20was%20totally%20outmaneuvered%20and%20withdrew%20in%20favour%20of%20Shastri%2C%20who%20became%20the%20prime%20minister%2C%20but%20Desai%20chose%20to%20remain%20out%20of%20his%20cabinet.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20role%20of%20kingmaker%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EKamaraj%20was%20destined%20to%20play%20the%20role%20of%20the%20kingmaker%20in%20less%20than%20two%20years.%20Shastri%20died%20at%20Tashkent%20on%20January%2011%2C%201966%20after%20signing%20a%20peace%20treaty%20with%20Pakistan%20following%20the%20India-Pakistan%20War%20in%201965%2C%20in%20which%20he%20led%20the%20nation%20successfully%20with%20his%20inspiring%20slogan%20of%20%E2%80%98Jai%20Jawan%20Jai%20Kisan%E2%80%99.%20This%20time%20the%20contest%20was%20between%20Desai%20and%20Mrs.%20Gandhi.%20Despite%20appeals%20from%20many%20leaders%2C%20including%20Kamaraj%2C%20Desai%20refused%20to%20withdraw%20and%20forced%20a%20contest.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20election%20to%20the%20leader%20of%20the%20Congress%20Parliamentary%20Party%20(CPP)%20that%20followed%2C%20Mrs.%20Gandhi%2C%20with%20the%20support%20of%20Kamaraj%20and%20others%20like%20Jagjivan%20Ram%20and%20Y.B.%20Chavan%2C%20won%20by%20a%20margin%20of%20355-169%20votes.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20role%20of%20Kamaraj%20as%20kingmaker%20was%20still%20not%20over.%20In%20the%201967%20elections%2C%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20tally%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20reduced%20considerably%20and%20it%20lost%20power%20in%20as%20many%20as%20eight%20states%2C%20including%20Kamaraj%E2%80%99s%20own%20home%20state%20of%20Tamil%20Nadu.%20To%20keep%20the%20Congress%20ship%20stable%20in%20view%20of%20its%20narrow%20majority%2C%20Kamaraj%20suggested%20to%20Mrs.%20Gandhi%20to%20appoint%20Desai%20as%20the%20deputy%20prime%20minister.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMrs.%20Gandhi%20readily%20accepted%20the%20proposal%20but%20soon%20differences%20arose%20between%20her%20and%20the%20Kamaraj-led%20syndicate.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFollowing%20the%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20split%20in%201969%2C%20Kamaraj%20was%20a%20disillusioned%20person%20but%20managed%20to%20win%20his%20Lok%20Sabha%20seat%20from%20Nagercoil%20in%20alliance%20with%20Rajaji%2C%20his%20one-time%20foe.%20Soon%20he%20rebuilt%20relations%20with%20Mrs.%20Gandhi%20but%20his%20deteriorating%20health%20and%20the%20rise%20of%20MGR%20after%20the%20DMK%20split%20prevented%20Kamaraj%20from%20reviving%20the%20Congress%20in%20the%20state.%20He%20died%20on%20October%202%2C%201975%20and%20was%20posthumously%20awarded%20the%20Bharat%20Ratna%20in%201976%20by%20the%20Indira%20Gandhi%20government.%20His%20statue%20on%20Krishna%20Menon%20Marg%20was%20unveiled%20in%201985%20by%20then%20Prime%20Minister%20Rajiv%20Gandhi.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EPraveen%20Davar%20is%20a%20former%20army%20officer%2C%20columnist%2C%20and%20author%20of%3C%2Fem%3E%20Freedom%20Struggle%20and%20Beyond.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696347356000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F03171743%2Fimage-1371.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fkamarajs-journey-from-humble-beginnings-to-kingmaker%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22As%20chief%20minister%2C%20he%20oversaw%20post-independence%20%E2%80%9Cgolden%20age%E2%80%9D%20of%20Madras%20state.%20As%20Congr