d-kapoor-and-kriti-sanons-next-untitled-romantic-film-gets-a-new-release-date%2Farticleshow%2F104136445.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Kerala%20HC%20Refuses%20to%20Stay%20Conviction%20of%20Lakshadweep%20MP%20Mohammed%20Faizal%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2F29114222%2FFQJqC1CWQAA2PF0final.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Kerala%20high%20court%20on%20Tuesday%20refused%20to%20suspend%20the%20convction%20of%20Lakshadweep%20MP%20Mohammed%20Faizal%20in%20an%20attempt%20to%20murder%20but%20suspended%20his%20the%20sentence.%20The%20development%20leaves%20the%20Nationalist%20Congress%20Party%20(NCP)%20leader%20open%20to%20disqualification.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Fhigh-court%2Fkerala-high-court%2Fkerala-high-court-mp-mohammed-faizal-conviction-disqualification-of-mp-mla-criminal-antecedents-239226%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Justice%20N.%20Nagaresh%20said%20that%20criminalisation%20of%20election%20process%20is%20of%20grave%20concern%20to%20democracy%20and%20if%20persons%20with%20criminal%20antecedents%20are%20permitted%20to%20continue%20as%20elected%20representatives%20even%20after%20conviction%20by%20a%20competent%20court%2C%20%E2%80%9Cthat%20would%20only%20send%20wrong%20signals%20to%20public%20at%20large%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%20data-reader-unique-id%3D%5C%2214%5C%22%3EThe%20judge%20said%20that%20the%20conviction%20can%20only%20be%20suspended%20under%20section%20389%20of%20the%20Code%20of%20Criminal%20Procedure%20(CrPC)%20if%20the%20Court%20was%20satisfied%20that%20the%20case%20was%20frivolous.%20He%20said%20conviction%20can%20be%20suspended%20if%20the%20court%20is%20satisfied%20that%20the%20convicted%20person%20%E2%80%9Cdoes%20not%20suffer%20from%20a%20certain%20disqualification%20or%20damage%20that%20cannot%20be%20undone%E2%80%9D%20only%20in%20rare%20cases%2C%20under%20special%20circumstances.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%20data-reader-unique-id%3D%5C%2214%5C%22%3EThe%20high%20court%20relied%20on%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20recent%20decision%20to%20suspend%20the%20conviction%20of%20Rahul%20Gandhi%2C%20which%20said%20that%20conviction%20%E2%80%9Ccannot%20be%20suspended%20by%20only%20looking%20at%20the%20ramifications%E2%80%9D%20but%20after%20considering%20all%20relevant%20aspects.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20January%20this%20year%2C%20Faizal%20and%20three%20others%20were%20convicted%20for%20attempting%20to%20murder%20a%20Congress%20leader%E2%80%99s%20son-in-law%20during%20the%202009%20general%20elections.%20The%20court%20sentenced%20him%20to%2010%20years%20in%20jail%2C%20which%20led%20to%20his%20automatic%20disqualified%20from%20the%20Lok%20Sabha.%20A%20couple%20of%20weeks%20later%2C%20another%20single-judge%20bench%20of%20the%20Kerala%20high%20court%20suspended%20his%20conviction.%20The%20thrust%20of%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20order%20was%20on%20the%20expenditure%20to%20the%20exchequer%20that%20the%20by-election%20would%20cause.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20August%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-mohammed-faizal-mp-suspension-set-aside%5C%22%3Eset%20aside%20that%20order%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20asking%20the%20high%20court%20to%20consider%20the%20matter%20afresh.%20It%20said%20that%20if%20the%20high%20court%E2%80%99s%20reasoning%20was%20allowed%20to%20stand%2C%20the%20conviction%20and%20sentence%20of%20every%20elected%20politicians%20would%20have%20to%20be%20suspended%20to%20avoid%20the%20financial%20burden%20of%20bye-elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696338853000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2F29114222%2FFQJqC1CWQAA2PF0final.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fkerala-hc-refuses-stay-conviction-lakshadweep-mp-mohammed-faizal%22%2C%22summary%22