0escalate%E2%80%9D%20the%20diplomatic%20spat%20with%20India.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAsked%20if%20Ottawa%20would%20retaliate%20if%20Canada%20had%20to%20remove%20diplomat%2C%20Trudeau%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cbc.ca%2Fnews%2Fpolitics%2Findia-canada-expel-diplomats-escalate-1.6984817%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EWe%E2%80%99re%20not%20looking%20to%20escalate%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20as%20I%E2%80%99ve%20said%2C%20we%E2%80%99re%20going%20to%20be%20doing%20the%20work%20that%20matters%20in%20continuing%20to%20have%20constructive%20relations%20with%20India%20through%20this%20extremely%20difficult%20time.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EStating%20that%20Canada%E2%80%99s%20relationship%20with%20India%20was%20%E2%80%9Cgoing%20through%20an%20extremely%20challenging%20time%E2%80%9D%2C%20Trudeau%20said%20that%20it%20even%20more%20%E2%80%9Cimportant%20for%20us%20to%20have%20diplomats%20on%20the%20ground%20working%20with%20the%20Indian%20government%20there%20to%20support%20Canadians%20and%20Canadian%20families.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECanada%20has%20several%20dozen%20more%20diplomats%20at%20its%20high%20commission%20in%20New%20Delhi%20than%20India%20has%20in%20Ottawa%2C%20because%20of%20the%20big%20consular%20section%20needed%20for%20relatives%20of%20the%20roughly%201.3%20million%20Canadians%20who%20claim%20Indian%20heritage%2C%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EFT%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20report%20says.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20per%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ECBC%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20Trudeau%20stated%20that%20his%20government%20was%20taking%20the%20diplomatic%20dispute%20%E2%80%9Cextremely%20seriously%E2%80%9D%20and%20is%C2%A0going%20to%20continue%20to%20try%20and%20%E2%80%9Cengage%20responsibly%20and%20constructively%E2%80%9D%20with%20India%20to%20sort%20it%20out.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20High%20commission%20of%20Canada%20in%20New%20Delhi%20told%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20it%20cannot%20comment.%20Similarly%2C%20the%20Ministry%20of%20External%20Affairs%20has%20also%20declined%20to%20comment%20on%20the%20%3Cem%3EFT%3C%2Fem%3E%20report.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20per%20earlier%20media%20reports%2C%20Canadian%20intelligence%20had%20communications%20to%20show%20that%20Indian%20diplomats%20in%20Canada%20were%20involved%20in%20the%20Nijjar%20killing.%20The%20US%20ambassador%20to%20Canada%2C%20David%20Cohen%20told%20Canadian%20broadcaster%20that%20intelligence%20from%20the%20Five%20Eyes%20countries%20had%20contributed%20to%20Trudeau%20going%20public%20with%20the%20%E2%80%9Ccredible%20allegations%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20United%20States%20has%20asked%20India%20to%20join%20the%20Canadian%20investigation%2C%20which%20was%20also%20reiterated%20when%20Indian%20external%20affairs%20minister%20S%20Jaishankar%20was%20in%20Washington%20last%20week.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%20Tuesday%2C%20deputy%20US%20State%20Department%20spokesman%20Vedant%20Patel%20said%2C%C2%A0%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20and%20continue%20to%20be%20deeply%20concerned%20about%20the%20allegations%20referenced%20by%20Prime%20Minister%20Trudeau%20and%20we%20remain%20in%20regular%20contact%20with%20our%20Canadian%20partners.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%E2%80%99s%20critical%20that%20Canada%E2%80%99s%20investigation%20proceed%20and%20the%20perpetrators%20be%20brought%20to%20justice.%20We%20also%20have%2C%20as%20we%E2%80%99ve%20previously%20said%2C%20publicly%20and%20privately%20urged%20the%20Indian%20government%20to%20co-operate%20in%20the%20Canadian%20investigation%20and%20co-operate%20in%20those%20efforts%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Indian%20government%20has%20repeatedly%20said%20that%20it%20will%20be%20willing%20to%20look%20at%20any%20evidence%2C%20but%20had%20claimed%20that%20none%20has%20been%20shared%20so%20far.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAccording%20to%20the%20%3Cem%3EFT%3C%2Fem%3E%20report%2C%20Canada%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eis%20limited%20in%20what%20it%20can%20share%20with%20the%20Indian%20government%2C%20partly%20to%20protect%20the%20sources%20and%20methods%20used%20to%20collect%20the%20intelligence%2C%20but%20also%20to%20avoid%20compromising%20the%20murder%20investigation%2C%20according%20to%20people%20familiar%20with%20the%20matter.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20constraints%20meant%20Thomas%20and%20other%20officials%20who%20visited%20India%2C%20including%20Canadian%20Security%20Intelligence%20Service%20head%20David%20Vigneault%2C%20had%20only%20been%20able%20to%20present%20the%20evidence%20verbally%20to%20their%20Indian%20counterparts%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELast%20week%2C%20Jaishankar%20had%20said%20that%20assassinations%20were%20%E2%80%9Cnot%20consistent%20with%20our%20policy%E2%80%9D.%20He%20also%20alleged%20that%20Canada%20did%20not%20take%20India%E2%80%99s%20concerns%20about%20Khalistani%20activities%20seriously%20and%20neither%20did%20they%20take%20steps%20to%20target%20groups%20that%20were%20specifically%20targeting%20Indian%20diplomats.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ENote%3A%20Additional%20informationw%20as%20added%20to%20this%20article%20after%20it%20was%20published.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696332593000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F19022725%2FScreenshot-2023-09-19-at-2.26.30-AM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Findia-asks-canada-to-repatriate-around-40-diplomats-report%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22India%20had%20earlier%20said%20that%20it%20had%20requested%20parity%20in%20diplomatic%20representation%20and%20that%20the%20two%20sides%20were%20holding%20talks%20to%20ensure%20this.%2