0is%20the%20proportion%20of%20seats%20held%20by%20women%20in%20national%20parliaments%20and%20local%20governments.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%20September%2020%2C%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20passed%20the%20Women%E2%80%99s%20Reservation%20Bill%2C%2027%20years%20after%20it%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Flok-sabha-passes-womens-reservation-bill%2Farticle67327458.ece%5C%22%3Ewas%20first%20introduced%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20parliament.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20unanimous%20support%20received%20in%20both%20Houses%20of%20Parliament%20for%20the%20Bill%2C%20which%20seeks%20to%20reserve%2033%25%20of%20seats%20for%20women%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20state%20legislative%20assemblies%2C%20underscores%20the%20potential%20impact%20of%20the%20Bill%20on%20improving%20women%E2%80%99s%20lives%20and%20their%20participation%20in%20public%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.weforum.org%2Freports%2Fglobal-gender-gap-report-2023%2Fin-full%2Fbenchmarking-gender-gaps-2023%2F%5C%22%3EGlobal%20Gender%20Gap%20Report%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20India%20stands%20at%20a%20low%2036.7%25%20on%20gender%20parity%20related%20to%20%E2%80%98economic%20participation%20and%20opportunity.%E2%80%99%20Despite%20achieving%20parity%20in%20enrollment%20across%20all%20levels%20of%20education%2C%20the%20same%20cannot%20be%20said%20for%20gender%20parity%20in%20health%20and%20survival.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIndia%20ranks%20142%20out%20of%20146%20countries%20on%20the%20health%20and%20survival%20sub-index.%20India%20also%20performs%20poorly%20on%20the%20political%20empowerment%20sub-index.%20In%20this%20context%2C%20the%20passage%20of%20the%20Bill%20is%20significant%2C%20given%20that%20the%20share%20of%20women%20parliamentarians%20has%20never%20crossed%20the%2015%25%20mark%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%2070-year-old%20electoral%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Flok-sabha-passes-womens-reservation-bill-amit-shah-implementation-2029%5C%22%3ELok%20Sabha%20Passes%20Women%E2%80%99s%20Reservation%20Bill%2C%20Amit%20Shah%20Confirms%20Implementation%20Not%20Before%202029%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20does%20India%20compare%20to%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world%20on%20political%20empowerment%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20United%20Nations%20(UN)%2C%20as%20of%20January%201%2C%202023%2C%20women%20hold%20executive%20positions%20in%2031%20nations%2C%20and%20in%2034%20nations%2C%20women%20hold%20the%20titles%20of%20Head%20of%20State%20or%20Head%20of%20Government.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww3.weforum.org%2Fdocs%2FWEF_GGGR_2023.pdf%5C%22%3EThe%20Global%20Gender%20Gap%20Index%20(GCCI)%20for%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%20highlights%20the%20largest%20gender%20gap%20in%20the%20%E2%80%98Political%20Empowerment%E2%80%99%20sub-index%2C%20with%20only%2022.1%25%20of%20the%20gap%20closed%20and%20a%20significant%20variation%20in%20scores%20among%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAmong%20countries%20using%20reservation%20quotas%2C%20Rwanda%20leads%20with%20the%20highest%20percentage%20of%20women%20in%20its%20national%20legislative%20chamber%2C%20where%20women%20hold%2061.3%25%20of%20the%20seats.%20Cuba%20and%20Nicaragua%20follow%20closely%20at%2055.7%25%20and%2051.7%25%2C%20respectively.%20In%20contrast%2C%20India%20has%20achieved%2025.3%25%20parity%20in%20the%20political%20empowerment%20sub-indicator%2C%20with%20women%20representing%20only%2015.1%25%20of%20parliamentarians.%20While%20this%20marks%20the%20highest%20level%20for%20India%20since%20the%20inaugural%202006%20edition%20of%20GGGI%2C%20it%20is%20disconcerting%20to%20note%20that%2C%20at%20the%20current%20rate%20of%20progress%20from%202006%20to%202023%2C%20achieving%20political%20empowerment%20for%20women%20in%20India%20remains%20a%20distant%20dream%20for%20another%20162%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20context%2C%20the%20Bill%20holds%20great%20promise%20for%20promoting%20gender%20equality%20and%20women%E2%80%99s%20empowerment.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20there%20are%20several%20challenges%20in%20this%20Bill.%20There%20is%20no%20linear%20pathway%20from%20having%20reserved%20quotas%20for%20women%20to%20achieving%20political%20decision-making%20and%20empowerment.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20analysis%20aims%20to%20address%20the%20complexities%20of%20reserved%20quotas%20and%20the%20gendered%20dimensions%20of%20ministerial%20portfolios%20held.%20It%20will%20also%20cover%20the%20significant%20barriers%20faced%20by%20women%20in%20politics%20including%20the%20question%20of%20intersectionality%20and%20violence.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwomen%2Fretracing-a-history-the-antecedents-of-the-womens-reservation-bill%5C%22%3EThe%20Women%20of%20the%20Women%E2%80%99s%20Reservation%20Bill%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20problem%20with%20reserved%20quotas%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESome%20women%E2%80%99s%20rights%20advocates%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwomen%2Fretracing-a-history-the-antecedents-of-the-womens-reservation-bill%5C%22%3Eargue%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20gender%20quotas%20can%20hinder%20women%E2%80%99s%20political%20empowerment%20by%20implying%20that%20they%20cannot%20succeed%20without%20special%20provisions.%20Concerns%20also%20exist%20about%20quotas%20diverting%20attention%20from%20the%20representation%20of%20other%20minority%20groups%2C%20potentially%20leading%20to%20similar%20demands%20for%20quotas%20from%20other%20marginalised%20communities.%20In%20this%20context%2C%20in%20India%2C%20the%20Women%E2%80%99s%20Reservation%20Bill%20faces%20challenges%20related%20to%20both%20horizontal%20and%20vertical%20reservations.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHorizontal%20reservation%20reserves%20seats%20for%20women%20in%20parliament%2C%20emphasising%20gender%20equity%20and%20gender-conscious%20policymaking.%20Vertical%20reservation%2C%20specifically%20for%20Other%20Backward%20Classes%20within%20the%20women%E2%80%99s%20quota%2C%20raises%20concerns%20about%20the%20representation%20of%20marginalised%20communities%2C%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Flok-sabha-passes-womens-reservation-bill%2Farticle67327458.ece%5C%22%3Ewas%20observed%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20demands%20raised%20by%20opposition%20parties%20for%20a%20separate%20OBC%20sub-quota%20within%20the%20reserved%20quota%20for%20women.%20They%20argue%20that%20OBCs%20constitute%20nearly%2040%25%20of%20the%20population%2C%20but%20unlike%20Scheduled%20Castes%20(SCs)%20and%20Scheduled%20Tribes%20(STs)%2C%20they%20have%20no%20separate%20reservation%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20state%20legislative%20assemblies.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Futtar-pradesh-upper-caste-obc-woman-reservation-election-mp-mla%5C%22%3Erecent%20article%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%3Cem%3E%20The%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20highlighted%20how%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20the%20largest%20state%20legislature%20in%20the%20country%2C%20has%20elected%20more%20women%20from%20%E2%80%98upper%E2%80%99%20castes%20as%20MLAs%20and%20MPs%20compared%20to%20OBCs%2C%20who%20are%20numerically%20more%20dominant.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThus%2C%20while%20gender%20quotas%20can%20be%20a%20tool%20for%20achieving%20representation%2C%20they%20come%20with%20complexities%20and%20potential%20unintended%20consequences%20that%20require%20careful%20consideration.%20The%20question%20of%20intersectionalities%20in%20a%20caste-ridden%20society%20cannot%20be%20overlooked%2C%20and%20the%20Women%E2%80%99s%20Reservation%20Bill%20should%20not%20end%20up%20disproportionately%20privileging%20upper-caste%20urban%20women.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20is%20political%20representation%20not%20enough%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Bill%20guarantees%20women%E2%80%99s%20representation%20in%20politics%2C%20but%20the%20challenge%20lies%20in%20establishing%20institutional%20arrangements%20that%20enable%20women%20to%20act%20independently%2C%20avoiding%20tokenism%20and%20patriarchal%20patronage.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESocietal%20norms%20still%20pose%20significant%20obstacles%20to%20women%E2%80%99s%20effective%20participation%2C%20with%20barriers%20like%20limited%20access%20to%20education%2C%20lack%20of%20childcare%20support%2C%20and%20financial%20constraints.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDiscriminatory%20tactics%20by%20political%20parties%2C%20voter%20and%20party%20leader%20bias%20against%20women%2C%20and%20concerns%20about%20female%20candidates%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%98electability%E2%80%99%20also%20persist.%20While%20the%20Bill%20shifts%20demand-side%20barriers%20in%20favour%20of%20women%20candidates%2C%20ensuring%20effective%20participation%20with%20the%20newly%20created%20critical%20mass%20of%20women%20in%20parliament%20is%20a%20challenge%2C%20given%20the%20lack%20of%20political%20education%20among%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20also%20the%20additional%20problem%20of%20gender%20stereotypes%20that%20influence%20portfolio%20allocations%2C%20hindering%20women%20from%20holding%20key%20roles.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ipu.org%2Fnews%2Fpress-releases%2F2023-03%2Fwomen-in-power-in-2023-new-data-shows-progress-wide-regional-gaps%5C%22%3EInter-Parliamentary%20Union%20(IPU)%202023%20press%20release%3C%2Fa%3E%20shows%20that%20women%20have%20high%20representation%20in%20portfolios%20like%20women%20and%20gender%20equality%2C%20family%20and%20children%20affairs%2C%20social%20inclusion%20and%20development%2C%20indigenous%20and%20minority%20affairs.%20However%2C%20critical%20policy%20areas%20such%20as%20economic%2C%20defence%2C%20justice%2C%20and%20home%20affairs%20are%20dominated%20by%20men.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F07%2F24175237%2FIMG_3927.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F07%2F24175237%2FIMG_3927.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F07%2F24175237%2FIMG_3927-300x120.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F07%2F24175237%2FIMG_3927-1024x410.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-542308%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22480%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EIllustration%3A%20Pariplab%20Chakraborty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPolitical%20violence%3Cbr%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcrsreports.congress.gov%2Fproduct%2Fpdf%2FR%2FR45483%5C%22%3Erecent%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Political%20Violence%20Targeting%20Women%2C%20women%20candidates%20for%20office%20globally%20experience%20up%20to%208%25%20violence%2C%20while%20female%20politicians%20experience%2012%25.%20Political%20party%20supporters%20face%2024%25%20violence%2C%20women%20voters%202%25%2C%20and%20government%20officials%20experience%2016%25%20of%20political%20violence%20attacks.%20Activists%2C%20human%20rights%20defenders%2C%20and%20social%20leaders%20experience%20the%20highest%20violence%2C%20accounting%20for%2038%25%20of%20political%20violence%20attacks.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIronically%2C%20the%20study%20notes%20that%20data%20on%20violence%20targeting%20women%20in%20politics%20are%20restricted%20to%20acts%20of%20physical%20violence%20against%20women%20in%20public%20settings%20during%20their%20engagement%20in%20the%20political%20process.%20It%20does%20not%20include%20acts%20of%20bullying%20or%20intimidation%2C%20cases%20of%20domestic%20violence%2C%20or%20virtual%20aggressive%20actions.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.unwomen.org%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2FHeadquarters%2FAttachments%2FSections%2FLibrary%2FPublications%2F2014%2FViolence%2520Against%2520Women%2520in%2520Politics-Report.pdf%5C%22%3EUN%20Women%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Violence%20against%20Women%20in%20Politics%20highlights%20how%20women%20who%20participate%20in%20politics%20and%20public%20life%20are%20perceived%20as%20a%20threat%20to%20the%20male%20superior%20status%2C%20resulting%20in%20violence%20against%20them.%20This%20serves%20as%20a%20significant%20barrier%20for%20women%E2%80%99s%20participation%20in%20the%20political%20process.%20It%20must%20also%20be%20noted%20that%20men%20with%20registered%20records%20of%20violence%20against%20women%20(as%20well%20as%20other%20types%20of%20criminal%20offences)%20are%20allowed%20to%20participate%20in%20politics.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20regard%2C%20it%20is%20disturbing%20to%20note%20that%20a%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fadrindia.org%2Fcontent%2F%25E2%2580%2598134-mps-mlas-have-cases-crime-against-women%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20Association%20of%20Democratic%20Reforms%20(ADR)%20revealed%20that%20a%20total%20of%20113%20MLAs%20and%2021%20MPs%20have%20declared%20cases%20of%20crimes%20against%20women%2C%20with%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20leading%20the%20statistics%20followed%20by%20the%20Congress%20party.%20Such%20statistics%20demand%20stringent%20measures%20to%20be%20adopted%20toward%20the%20decriminalisation%20of%20politics%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Nari%20Shakti%20Vandana%20Adhiniyam%20Bill%20represents%20a%20crucial%20step%20towards%20enhancing%20women%E2%80%99s%20political%20representation%20in%20India.%20Quotas%20for%20women%20have%20been%20shown%20to%20improve%20public%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Fopinion%2Fwomen-s-reservation-bill-will-bridge-the-gender-gap-in-political-decision-making-in-india%2Fstory-DrJt5apRR5J9UoqeB3CXHO.html%5C%22%3Espending%20on%20services%20that%20matter%20to%20them%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20such%20as%20drinking%20water%2C%20sanitation%2C%20public%20health%2C%20primary%20education%2C%20and%20roads%2C%20as%20demonstrated%20in%20the%20case%20of%20gram%20panchayats.%20Studies%20have%20also%20indicated%20that%20a%20higher%20representation%20of%20women%20in%20parliament%20leads%20to%20the%20passing%20of%20more%20gender-sensitive%20laws%20on%20issues%20like%20sexual%20harassment%2C%20rape%2C%20and%20domestic%20violence.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20India%2C%20local%20female%20leaders%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20advocate%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcarnegieendowment.org%2F2023%2F09%2F26%2Findia-s-new-gender-quota-law-is-win-for-women-mostly-pub-90644%5C%22%3Egender-equal%20property%20inheritance%20laws%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20Bill%2C%20by%20itself%2C%20cannot%20achieve%20significant%20progress%20in%20women%E2%80%99s%20empowerment%20unless%20efforts%20are%20made%20to%20address%20deep-rooted%20patriarchal%20norms%20that%20assign%20women%20low%20status%20in%20society%2C%20keep%20them%20out%20of%20the%20labour%20force%2C%20burden%20them%20disproportionately%20with%20unpaid%20domestic%20and%20care%20work%2C%20and%20use%20violence%20as%20a%20means%20of%20repression%20or%20discipline.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20passage%20of%20the%20Bill%20is%20a%20beacon%20of%20hope%2C%20but%20realising%20its%20full%20potential%20requires%20concerted%20efforts%20to%20overcome%20these%20hurdles%20and%20create%20a%20more%20inclusive%20and%20equitable%20political%20landscape%20for%20women%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDivya%20Pradeep%20and%20Roopa%20Patavardhan%20teach%20Economics%20at%20Christ%20University%2C%20Bengaluru.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696331715000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F26191526%2F1280px-View_of_Lok_Sabha_chamber_in_the_New_Parliament_building_New_Delhi.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwomen%2Fwomens-reservation-bill-significant-concerted-efforts-empowerment%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20share%20of%20women%20parliamentarians%20has%20never%20crossed%20the%2015%25%20mark%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%2070-year-old%20electoral%20history.%20To%20achieve%20significant%20progress%20in%20women's%20empowerment%2C%20deep-rooted%20patriarchal%20norms%20that%20assign%20women%20low%20status%20in%20society%20need%20to%20be%20addressed.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwomen%2Fwomens-reservation-bill-significant-concerted-efforts-empowerment%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20BJP's%20Own%20Fragmenting%20of%20Social%20Justice%20Politics%20Led%20to%20the%20Bihar%20Caste%20Census%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F01%2F17103022%2FModi-Shah.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20larger%20takeaway%20from%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fnarendra-modi-caste-census-speech%5C%22%3Estatement%20that%20opposition%20forces%20have%20divided%20India%20along%20caste%20lines%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20continue%20to%20%E2%80%9Ccommit%20that%20sin%E2%80%9D%20was%20not%20lost%20on%20anybody.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%2C%20thus%2C%20tacitly%2C%20declared%20his%20opposition%20to%20the%20demand%20for%20a%20caste%20census%20on%20the%20day%20when%20the%20Bihar%20government%20released%20the%20results%20of%20its%20recently-concluded%20caste%20census%2C%20comprehensively%20outlining%20data%20on%20the%20caste%20make-up%20of%20the%20state.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20should%20one%20consider%20the%20prime%20minister%E2%80%99s%20statement%20as%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20official%20position%20on%20caste%20census%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20It%20will%20be%20difficult%20to%20assume%20so%20because%20a%20range%20of%20senior%20BJP%20leaders%20have%20pedalled%20different%20views%20on%20it.%20Senior%20leader%20and%20Union%20minister%20Giriraj%20Singh%20has%20said%20that%20the%20Bihar%20chief%20minister%20Nitish%20Kumar%20was%20trying%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.abplive.com%2Fstates%2Fbihar-caste-census-report-cm-nitish-congratulates-survey-team-giriraj-singh-calls-it-just-an-eye-wash-lalu-prasad-yadav-1633279%5C%22%3Emislead%3C%2Fa%3E%20people%20through%20a%20caste%20census%2C%20while%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20senior-most%20saffron%20leader%20and%20Rajya%20Sabha%20MP%20Sushil%20Kumar%20Modi%20has%20said%20that%20the%20process%20of%20counting%20caste%20groups%20in%20Bihar%20was%20actually%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20doing%20when%20the%20party%20was%20Nitish%20Kumar%E2%80%99s%20ally%20in%20the%20state%20government.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBJP%E2%80%99s%20Bihar%20unit%20president%20Samrat%20Choudhary%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20exercised%20some%20restraint%20and%20said%20that%20the%20party%20will%20take%20a%20position%20only%20after%20studying%20the%20%E2%80%9Cmethodology%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20census%20process.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20light%20of%20such%20contradictory%20remarks%20coming%20out%20of%20the%20saffron%20camp%2C%20it%20is%20safe%20to%20assume%20that%20the%20BJP%20hasn%E2%80%99t%20been%20able%20to%20formulate%20a%20clear%20position%20on%20the%20issue%20of%20a%20pan-India%20caste%20census%2C%20the%20demand%20for%20which%20the%20opposition%20parties%20have%20been%20consistently%20raising.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20clear%20to%20see%20that%20BJP%20is%20in%20a%20catch%2022%20situation.%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20campaign%20since%202014%20has%20made%20it%20a%20point%20to%20reach%20out%20to%20non-dominant%20Other%20Backward%20Class%20and%20Dalit%20communities%20and%20bring%20them%20into%20the%20Hindutva%20tent.%20Occasional%20representatives%20belonging%20to%20these%20communities%20were%20nominated%20for%20top%20posts%2C%20in%20an%20attempt%20to%20gain%20their%20communities%E2%80%99%20confidence.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20the%20BJP%20also%20canvassed%20against%20agrarian%20caste%20groups%20like%20Yadavs%2C%20Marathas%2C%20and%20Jats%20and%20pitched%20them%20against%20non-dominant%20communities.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20process%2C%20the%20BJP%20was%20fairly%20successful%20in%20fragmenting%20OBC%20and%20Dalit%20communities%20as%20separate%20political%20groups.%20For%20instance%2C%20the%20non-Yadav%20OBC%20and%20non-Jatav%20Dalits%20of%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20were%20told%20by%20the%20BJP%20that%20most%20gains%20from%20Mandal-based%20affirmative%20action%20had%20been%20cornered%20by%20Yadavs.%20In%20Bihar%2C%20too%2C%20the%20BJP%20was%20partially%20successful%20in%20mobilising%20small%20caste-based%20communities%20like%20Kalwar%2C%20Dhobi%2C%20Sonar%2C%20Bania%20and%20others%20against%20Yadavs.%20The%20saffron%20party%20allied%20with%20single-caste%20parties%2C%20largely%20led%20by%20one%20or%20other%20non-dominant%20OBC%20groups%20which%20advocated%20greater%20political%20power%20for%20their%20communities.%20These%20parties%2C%20like%20Om%20Prakash%20Rajbhar%20Suheldev%20Bharatiya%20Samaj%20Party%2C%20Sanjay%20Nishad%E2%80%99s%20NISHAD%20party%2C%20Mukesh%20Sahni%E2%80%99s%20Vikassheel%20Insaan%20Party%2C%20or%20Anupriya%20Patel%E2%80%99s%20Apna%20Dal%20%E2%80%93%20even%20when%20they%20have%20been%20in%20the%20BJP-led%20NDA%20%E2%80%93%20have%20been%20strongly%20supporting%20the%20demand%20for%20a%20caste%20census%20or%20policies%20which%20may%20increase%20their%20share%20in%20political%20power.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fbihars-caste-census-nitish%5C%22%3EBihar%E2%80%99s%20Caste%20Census%20Is%20a%20Bold%20Move%20Sure%20to%20Have%20Implications%20Beyond%20the%20State%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20consolidation%20of%20such%20groups%20by%20the%20BJP%20was%20also%20combined%20with%20a%20parallel%20process%20of%20alienating%20these%20groups%20from%20Muslims%20through%20a%20shrill%20communal%20rhetoric.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20non-dominant%20communities%20were%20given%20to%20understand%20that%20it%20was%20not%20only%20dominant%20OBCs%20and%20Dalits%20like%20Yadavs%20and%20Jatavs%20who%20were%20responsible%20for%20their%20under-representation%20but%20also%20Muslims%20whose%20tactical%20support%20was%20necessary%20for%20social%20justice%20parties%20like%20the%20Samajwadi%20Party%20or%20Rashtriya%20Janata%20Dal%20to%20come%20to%20power.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20the%20Muslim-Yadav%20combination%2C%20the%20mainstay%20of%20parties%20like%20SP%20and%20RJD%20which%20are%20also%20the%20most%20vocal%20opponents%20of%20the%20BJP%20in%20the%20Hindi%20heartland%2C%20disintegrated%20under%20the%20expansive%20Hindutva%20umbrella.%20While%20BJP%20registered%20successive%20victories%20in%20northern%20India%20by%20riding%20on%20the%20newly-found%20support%20of%20under-represented%20OBC%20and%20Dalit%20groups%2C%20the%20Mandal-based%20parties%20faced%20one%20loss%20after%20another.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBJP%20could%20successfully%20exploit%20the%20chink%20in%20the%20armour%20of%20social%20justice%20parties%20which%20in%20the%201990s%20and%20early%202000s%20had%20stemmed%20the%20saffron%20party%E2%80%99s%20growth.%20By%20doubling%20down%20on%20this%20political%20strategy%2C%20Modi%20and%20senior%20BJP%20leaders%20did%20not%20miss%20even%20a%20single%20chance%20to%20break%20apart%20the%20Mandal%20parties%20that%20had%20until%20now%20carried%20social%20justice%20political%20rhetoric%20on%20their%20shoulders.%20If%20the%20Adityanath-led%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20government%20constituted%20a%20social%20justice%20commission%20to%20acknowledge%20the%20presence%20of%20non-dominant%20groups%2C%20the%20Modi-led%20Union%20government%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fas-justice-rohini-panel-submits-report-will-the-modi-govt-move-ahead-with-sub-quotas-for-obcs%5C%22%3Eformed%20the%20Justice%20G.%20Rohini%20Commission%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20explore%20the%20possibility%20of%20sub-categorisation%20of%20OBC%20groups.%20However%2C%20none%20of%20these%20reports%20have%20been%20released.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20such%20moves%20were%20clearly%20drawn%20from%20the%20social%20justice%20template%20%E2%80%93%20taking%20a%20leaf%20out%20of%20Nitish%20Kumar%E2%80%99s%20tactical%20decisions%20earlier%20to%20create%20EBC%20and%20Mahadalit%20categories%20in%20Bihar%20which%20helped%20him%20combat%20the%20Rashtriya%20Janata%20Dal%E2%80%99s%20formidable%20Yadav-Muslim%20social%20coalition%20in%20the%20first%20decade%20of%20the%20millennium.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20reluctance%20to%20implement%20the%20recommendations%20of%20these%20committees%20allowed%20the%20social%20justice%20parties%20to%20send%20a%20message%20that%20these%20commissions%20were%20formed%20as%20a%20ploy%20%E2%80%93%20to%20alienate%20agrarian%20caste%20groups%20further%20and%20weaken%20social%20justice%20politics%20%E2%80%93%20rather%20than%20to%20give%20the%20non-dominant%20OBC%20and%20Dalits%20groups%20their%20due%20share%20in%20power.%20Emboldening%20Hindutva%2C%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20critics%20said%2C%20was%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20primary%20goal%2C%20not%20social%20justice%20because%20of%20which%20many%20OBC%20and%20Dalit%20groups%20have%20veered%20towards%20the%20saffron%20party.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESocialist%20parties%20like%20the%20RJD%2C%20the%20SP%20and%20the%20Janata%20Dal%20(United)%20subsequently%20saw%20a%20window%20to%20intensify%20the%20rhetoric%20of%20social%20justice%20in%20such%20circumstances%2C%20and%20made%20the%20caste%20census%20their%20political%20plank.%20They%20argued%20that%20welfare%20measures%20could%20be%20better%20streamlined%20if%20the%20government%20knew%20the%20population%20and%20socio-economic%20indices%20of%20different%20communities%20in%20India.%20By%20demanding%20a%20caste%20census%2C%20the%20social%20justice%20parties%20acknowledged%20their%20past%20mistakes%20of%20prioritising%20dominant%20OBC%20groups%20over%20others.%20But%20the%20caste%20census%20also%20allowed%20them%20to%20see%20a%20democratic%20future%20for%20Lohiaite%20politics%20based%20on%20principles%20of%20equality%20and%20proportional%20representation%20of%20under-privileged%20communities.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fwhy-the-bjp-is-afraid-of-a-caste-census%5C%22%3EWhy%20the%20BJP%20Is%20Afraid%20of%20a%20Caste%20Census%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20wishy-washy%20approach%20towards%20a%20caste%20census%20shows%20the%20Modi%20government%E2%80%99s%20confusion.%20First%2C%20it%20opposed%20a%20caste%20census%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%202021%2C%20citing%20administrative%20and%20logistical%20reasons.%20More%20recently%2C%20the%20Centre%20argued%20in%20the%20apex%20court%20that%20only%20the%20Centre%20itself%20could%20conduct%20a%20caste%20census%20as%20it%20was%20a%20%E2%80%9CUnion%20subject%E2%80%9D%2C%20in%20an%20attempt%20to%20prevent%20states%20like%20Bihar%2C%20Odisha%20and%20Jharkhand%20from%20conducting%20their%20own%20caste%20census.%20However%2C%20it%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fbihar-caste-survey-case-state-govt-census-centre-tells-supreme-court-236420%5C%22%3Ewithdrew%20the%20affidavit%20almost%20immediately%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20citing%20that%20the%20line%20of%20argument%20was%20inadvertently%20introduced%20in%20it.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20the%20Union%20government%20introduced%20the%20Economically%20Weaker%20Section%20reservation%2C%20which%20effectively%20gives%20a%2010%25%20quota%20to%20only%20%E2%80%98upper%E2%80%99%20caste%20individuals%20whose%20annual%20income%20is%20less%20than%20Rs%208%20lakhs.%20It%20meant%20that%20%E2%80%98upper%E2%80%99%20caste%20groups%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Funcategorised%2Fbihar-caste-census-released-at-63-obc-ebc-groups-set-to-take-pole-position-in-state-politics%23%3A~%3Atext%3DPatna%253A%2520The%2520Bihar%2520government%2520finally%2C(EBC)%2520is%252026.01%2525.%5C%22%3Ewhich%20are%20a%20minority%20in%20the%20population%2C%20as%20the%20Bihar%20caste%20census%20clearly%20reveals%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20get%20a%20disproportionately%20higher%20share%20in%20the%20reservation%20system.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20move%20further%20muddied%20the%20waters.%20For%20instance%2C%20%E2%80%98upper%E2%80%99%20caste%20groups%20in%20states%20like%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20Karnataka%2C%20or%20even%20Andhra%20Pradesh%2C%20where%20they%20constitute%20less%20than%205%25%20of%20the%20total%20population%2C%20are%20entitled%20to%20a%2010%25%20reservation.%20Even%20in%20states%20like%20Bihar%20where%20they%20form%20a%20little%20over%2015%25%2C%20the%20EWS%20reservation%20allows%20them%20to%20get%20a%2010%25%20quota.%20In%20contrast%2C%20the%20OBC%20groups%20put%20together%20in%20Bihar%20form%20over%2063%25%20of%20the%20total%20population%20but%20can%20have%20only%2027%25%20reservation%20in%20government%20institutions.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENow%2C%20the%20PM%20has%20made%20a%20direct%20political%20statement%2C%20tacitly%20opposing%20caste%20census%2C%20but%20overlooking%20the%20multiple%20attempts%20by%20his%20own%20and%20other%20BJP-led%20state%20governments%20to%20devise%20ways%20for%20a%20caste%20count%20through%20various%20committees%20and%20policies.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESignificantly%2C%20the%20demand%20for%20a%20caste%20census%20was%20propelled%20by%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20efforts%20to%20fragment%20social%20justice%20parties%20for%20electoral%20gains.%20And%2C%20now%20that%20such%20politicking%20has%20allowed%20the%20opposition%20to%20give%20it%20an%20ideological%20shape%20and%20direction%2C%20the%20BJP%20finds%20itself%20scratching%20its%20head.%20Mandal%20politics%20successfully%20prevented%20Hindutva%20ideology%20from%20taking%20deep%20roots%20in%20India%20earlier.%20It%20took%20an%20OBC%20leader%2C%20Narendra%20Modi%2C%20to%20assimilate%20aspects%20of%20that%20ideology%20to%20give%20Hindutva%20a%20subaltern%20colour%20in%20the%20last%20decade.%20The%20demand%20for%20a%20pan-India%20caste%20census%20is%20a%20concrete%20attempt%20by%20social%20justice%20parties%20to%20reclaim%20their%20roots%20in%20Indian%20politics.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMandal%20politics%20began%20in%20the%201980s%20with%20a%20demand%20for%20OBC%20quota%20but%20is%20now%20claiming%20proportional%20representation%20in%20power%20corridors%2C%20something%20that%20the%20social%20justice%20parties%20have%20been%20calling%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3Ehissedari%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%9D%2C%20based%20on%20the%20famous%20Kanshi%20Ram%E2%80%99s%20slogan%2C%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3EJinki%20jitni%20sankhya%20bhaari%2C%20utni%20unki%20hissedari%3C%2Fem%3E.%E2%80%9D%20Translated%2C%20it%20means%2C%20t%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ehe%20greater%20a%20community%E2%80%99s%20numbers%2C%20the%20greater%20its%20political%20representation.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20caste%20census%20is%20truly%20a%20historic%20turn%20in%20the%20social%20justice%20movement%20of%20India.%20A%20Mandal%202.0%20moment.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696330986000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F01%2F17103022%2FModi-Shah.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fbjp-narendra-modi-social-justice-caste-census-obc-dalit%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Even%20though%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20has%20accused%20opposition%20parties%20of%20dividing%20the%20country%20along%20caste%20lines%2C%20it%20cannot%20be%20denied%20that%20BJP's%20success%20in%20exploiting%20the%20chink%20in%20the%20armour%20of%20social%20justice%20parties%20has%20now%20come%20to%20affect%20it.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A34%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fbjp-narendra-modi-social-justice-caste-census-obc-dalit%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Vedanta%20to%20complete%20sale%20of%20steel%20assets%20by%20March%202024%3A%20Anil%20Agarwal%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696330798000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2023-10%2F03%2Ffull%2F1696325042-351.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fvedanta-to-complete-sale-of-steel-assets-by-march-2024-anil-agarwal-123100300745_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20an%20interview%2C%20Agarwal%20said%20the%20response%20to%20the%20steel%20and%20iron%20business%20will%20help%20the%20company%20reduce%20debt%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fvedanta-to-complete-sale-of-steel-assets-by-march-2024-anil-agarwal-123100300745_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fvedanta-to-complete-sale-of-steel-assets-by-march-2024-anil-agarwal-123100300745_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fvedanta-to-complete-sale-of-steel-assets-by-march-2024-anil-agarwal-123100300745_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Lesser%20known%20facts%20about%20%E2%80%8BCrash%20Landing%20on%20You%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696330528000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-104131745%2Cimgsize-51744.cms%22%2C%22o